        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "# 🍅 Tomato Watering Guide\n\n## VWC Targets by Growth Stage\n\n| Stage | Target VWC | Water When Below | Notes |\n|-------|-----------|------------------|-------|\n| **Seedling** | 25–35% | 20% | Keep consistently moist, never dry |\n| **Vegetative** | 20–30% | 15% | Allow slight dry-down to encourage roots |\n| **Flowering** | 25–35% | 20% | Critical — stress causes blossom drop |\n| **Fruiting** | 25–40% | 20% | Even moisture prevents blossom end rot |\n| **Ripening** | 15–25% | 12% | Slight stress concentrates sugars |\n\n## Problems & Causes\n\n| Symptom | Likely Cause | Fix |\n|---------|-------------|-----|\n| **Blossom end rot** (black bottom on fruit) | VWC < 15% for >24h → calcium can't uptake | Water deeply, mulch, add gypsum |\n| **Cracked fruit** | VWC swings dry→suddenly wet | Water little & often, not big dumps |\n| **Yellow lower leaves** | VWC > 45% → root rot / anaerobic | Stop watering, check drainage holes |\n| **Wilting in afternoon** | Normal if VWC > 20% — heat, not drought | Check VWC before watering |\n| **Wilting + VWC < 15%** | Actual drought stress | Water immediately, shade until recovered |\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- **Water in morning** (6–9 AM) — leaves dry before evening, less disease\n- **Water at base**, not overhead — prevents fungal leaf spots\n- **Deep & infrequent** beats shallow & frequent — encourages deep roots\n- **Mulch** (straw, wood chips) — reduces evaporation by 50%, stabilises VWC\n- **Feed weekly** when fruiting — tomatoes are hungry |\n\n## Glasshouse-Specific\n\n- VWC drops **2× faster** in glasshouse than outside (heat + no rain)\n- Check daily in summer, every 2–3 days in spring/autumn\n- Ventilate on hot days — soil temp > 28°C reduces nutrient uptake",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
